  - family-names: "Retif"
    given-names: "Paul"
abstract: >-
  Python workflow for retrospective intrafraction motion verification using
  triggered kilovoltage images acquired during stereotactic body radiotherapy
  for bone metastases. The workflow generates angle-specific digitally
  reconstructed radiographs from the planning CT, preprocesses triggered kV
  images and DRRs, performs rigid in-plane registration, and exports
  image-level displacement estimates and quality-control visualizations.
keywords:
  - radiotherapy
  - stereotactic body radiotherapy
  - bone metastases
  - intrafraction motion
  - triggered kilovoltage imaging
  - image registration
  - digitally reconstructed radiograph
  - quality assurance
